Release Notes:

This double live album from one of Britain's most enduring and beloved heavy metal acts is the soundtrack to the rockumentary film of the same name which follows the band on their 2008 world tour, and which receives a simultaneous DVD release. After nearly 35 years, 14 studio albums and 70 million records sold, Maiden are still ripping it up like teenagers and this collection, taking in performances from Asia and the Americas, demonstrates both the showmanship and the ferocity of their live sets.
